{"name": "Scarpa Drago LV Rock Shoes - Unisex", "categories": ["Home", "All", "Climbing", "Climbing footwear", "Climbing shoes", "Drago LV Rock Shoes"], "description": "Super-sensitive and ridiculously aggressive for your next project. Purpose-built for sending steep technical boulders and overhanging lines, the Drago has a small, floating midsole for finger-like toe grabbing ability.Microsuede for a consistent fit over time.PCB (Power Connection Band) strap provides a \"sucked in\" fit at the arch.Rubber-wrapped forefoot for technical toe hooks and scumming.PAF heel system distributes the pressure on the heel for a comfortable fit.Vibram\u00ae XS Grip 2 rubber provides exceptional friction and outstanding sensitivity.Members typically downsize 1-1.5 sizes (performance fit) or 0.5-1 sizes (comfort fit) from their street shoe size.", "product_code": "6010-071", "tech_specs": {"Weight": ["400g (40)"], "Ideal for": ["Bouldering", "Sport and toprope climbing", "Indoor climbing"], "Type\n\nA neutral shoe suits long routes and cracks. Moderate shoes allow precision and good edging. Aggressive shoes are downturned and tensioned, for power to the toe on steep or overhanging routes.": ["Aggressive"], "Asymmetry\n\nHighly asymmetric shoes allow more precision and focused power. Symmetrical shoes are more comfortable for all-around climbing.": ["High"], "Stiffness\n\nStiffness is provided by the type of sole and the tensioning system. Softer shoes allow more precision. Supportive shoes prevent fatigue.": ["Soft"], "Uppers": ["Synthetic"], "Closure": ["Hook-and-loop"], "Outsoles": ["3.5mm Vibram XS Grip 2"], "Lined": ["No"], "Made in": ["Italy"]}, "img_urls": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9125063688222/6010071-WHT00.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9125068636190/6010071-WHT00-ALT-BACK-UNDER.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9125068668958/6010071-WHT00-ALT-OUTSIDE.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias